== Rice ==

Boil a large #pot{} of water for the rice.

Thoroughly rinse the @Brown Basmati Rice{1} under cold water for a minute. Add the rice to the boiling water with @salt{1/4%tsp} and cook for around ~{20-25%minutes} until soft.

> Once cooked, drain the rice, put back in the pot (off the heat) and cover with a clean
> tea towel for 5 mins.

== Vegetables ==

Meanwhile, finely chop the @Garlic Clove{2}(finely chopped) and @Red Chilli{1/2}(finely chopped). Peel the @Ginger{1.5}(peeled and finely chopped) with the edge of a #spoon{} and finely chop. Finely slice the @Spring Onion{3}(finely sliced, including the green part) and chop the @Chestnut Mushrooms{1}(chopped in half). Separate the @Broccoli{1/2}(separated into florets) from the stalk and cut them in half.

Boil another #pot{} of water for the broccoli. Cook the broccoli for about ~{3%minutes}, then drain.

== Kung Pao ==

To make the Kung Pao, whisk together the @Soy Sauce{3}(in a small bowl), @Rice Vinegar{2}(in a small bowl) and @?sugar{2%tsp} in a #small bowl{}.

Heat a #wok{} or large #frying pan{} over high heat and add @olive oil{1%tbsp}. When hot, add the broccoli and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the mushrooms and cook for a further ~{1-2%minutes} without moving the pan.

> If you stir the mushrooms too often they won't get nice and brown!

Add the garlic, chilli (as much as you dare!), ginger and three-quarters of the spring onion to the pan (reserving some of the green bits for later) and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add the Kung Pao mix and cook for a further ~{1%minute}, then remove the pan from the heat and stir in the @Cashew Nuts{2}.

== To Serve ==

Serve your rice into #bowls{}, top with your Kung Pao and the remaining spring onion. Tuck in!